## Flow

- The customer sends daily data to invent-beymen-input/ in Microsoft Azure Storage every day at 10.00 AM (it will be preponed later)
- The daily runner is scheduled for 11:30 AM. (it will be preponed later) Daily runner triggers daily DAG. When the daily DAG is triggered daily data is transfered from invent-beymen-input to invent-beymen-input/history folder.
- All files are pushed at once, no partial upload
- 21 files + 1 manifest receieved per day.
- Customer historical data is stored in invent-beymen-input-dev/HISTORICAL_DATA/backup.
- Beymen Daily Dag checks the manifest file.
- If the system cannot find the manifest file, it will assume that the files are not complete. If there are missing files with the Critical column is No in the following table, related tasks can be marked success, and the latest data in the datastore can be used.
- If there are missing files with the Critical column is Yes in the following table, you should contact with customer.
